      "inputs": {},
      "extra_files": {
        "text": {
          "content": "2\n*\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0002\u0000\u0000\u0002iFacet POP can make every vertex of every primitive be a unique point. \n\nWhen doing so, the normals of the points change since they are not longer shared with adjacent primitives.  Therefore the Compute Point Normals parameter is on by default, but if you som't care about normals, turn it of to gain some speed.\n\nnull_normalVectors0 and null_normalVectors1 show this difference.\n\nThe same is true when going fro unique points back to shared points when Operation is Consolidate Points. (facet2)\n\nfacet3 makes the points unique if the angle between adjacent polygons exceeds a certain value, in this case 14 degrees.\n\n",
          "is_binary": false
        }
      }
    },
